Reasoning: The paper discusses the modelling and control of a Flapping Wing Micro Air Vehicle (FW MAV), which falls under the category of Robotics (cs.RO). The use of Fuzzy C-Means (FCM) clustering algorithm for modelling and developing an adaptive fuzzy controller suggests the involvement of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) techniques. The adaptive nature of the controller also indicates the involvement of System and Control Theory (cs.SY). Additionally, the use of clustering algorithm and fuzzy logic can also be related to Neural Networks (cs.NE).
